-----Pixel-Edge-Marketing-Dashboard

-----1)Project Title
Designed an interactive dashboard to analyze campaign performance, channel efficiency, geographic trends, and ROI using KPIs, funnel analysis, and geographic mapping.

-----2) Purpose
     The primary purpose of this dashboard is to monitor, analyze, and optimize marketing performance across multiple campaigns, channels, regions, and countries in order to maximize revenue,
     improve ROI, and support data-driven decision-making.

-----3) Tech Stack
     The dashboard was built using the following tools and technologies:

     Power BI Desktop: Main data visualization platform used for report creation.

     Power Query: Data transformation and cleaning layer for reshaping and preparing the data.

     DAX (Data Analysis Expressions): Used for calculated measures, dynamic visuals, and conditional logic.

     Data Modeling: Relationships established among tables to enable cross-filtering and aggregation.

     File Format: .pbix for development and .png for dashboard previews

-----4) Data Source
     This dashboard is built using sample/synthetic data modeled to represent Marketing-like operations.

-----5) Features and Highlights
-----5.1) Bussiness Problem
     This dashboard solves critical business problems related to ROI visibility, budget optimization, campaign effectiveness, geographic performance, and executive reporting.

-----5.2) Goal Of The DashBoard
     The goal of this dashboard is to provide a centralized, data-driven view of marketing performance that enables stakeholders to measure ROI, optimize campaigns, 
     allocate budgets effectively, and drive revenue growth across channels and geographies.

-----5.3) Walk Through The Key Visuals
     The purpose of the Total Revenue KPI card is to provide an instant, high-level view of the total income generated from marketing activities within a selected time period, 
     helping stakeholders quickly assess whether marketing efforts are contributing to business growth.

     The purpose of the Total Spend KPI card is to provide an instant summary of how much money has been invested in marketing activities over a selected period, 
     helping stakeholders monitor budget usage and control marketing costs.

     The purpose of the CTR (%) KPI card is to measure how effectively marketing ads and campaigns are engaging the target audience by showing the percentage of users
     who clicked on an ad after seeing it.

     The purpose of the Total Conversions KPI card is to show the total number of desired actions completed by users (such as purchases, sign-ups, or leads), 
     indicating how effectively marketing efforts are driving actual business outcomes.

     The purpose of the Segment by Conversions pie chart is to show how total conversions are distributed across different customer segments, helping stakeholders understand which segments 
     contribute most to successful outcomes.

     The Leads by Campaign donut chart shows how leads are distributed across campaigns, helping identify top lead-generating campaigns and guide budget and optimization decisions.

     The purpose of the Spend by Channel stacked column chart is to compare how marketing spend is distributed across channels and categories 
     (such as campaigns, regions, or customer segments), enabling stakeholders to understand where money is being spent and how that spend is allocated.

     The purpose of the Revenue by Region clustered bar chart is to compare revenue performance across multiple regions and sub-categories (like campaigns, channels, or customer segments)
     to help stakeholders identify high-performing markets and areas that need attention.

     The purpose of the Region slicer is to allow users to filter the entire dashboard based on a specific region or multiple regions, 
     so stakeholders can focus on the performance of one area at a time and make regional-level decisions.

     The Monthly Revenue per Year line chart visualizes revenue trends across months and years, helping stakeholders detect seasonality, assess growth, 
     and plan marketing strategies effectively.

     The Monthly Conversions per Year line chart tracks how conversions change month by month across years, helping stakeholders identify seasonality, evaluate marketing effectiveness,
     and optimize campaigns for maximum impact.

     The purpose of a Geo Distribution Map is to visualize marketing performance, revenue, or conversions geographically, allowing stakeholders to understand regional trends, 
     identify high- and low-performing areas, and make location-specific marketing decisions.

     The Monthly Revenue and Spend clustered column chart compares marketing investment against revenue each month, enabling stakeholders to assess ROI trends, detect seasonality, 
     and make data-driven budget decisions.

     The Clicks by Channel treemap visualizes user engagement across marketing channels, helping stakeholders identify top-performing channels, detect underperforming ones, 
     and make data-driven decisions for budget allocation and campaign optimization.


-----5.4) Bussiness Impact And Insight
     This marketing dashboard transforms raw marketing data into actionable insights, helping stakeholders optimize campaigns, allocate budgets efficiently, improve ROI, 
     identify top-performing regions and customer segments, and make data-driven strategic decisions.

